22934,"What is the best way to model one-to-many relationship, when you cannot use embedded document in MongoDB?

Let's say you have a video, and each video can have comments, obviously, that is a one-to-many relationship. The simplest way to model that in Mongo is to use embedded documents. However, if you have thousands of comments, that would become just terrible.
• Store comment ids in a list in video document
The first one has a problem of what happens if multiple users try to update the comment id list at the same time, chances are some data and ids will be lost, so not the best option.
The second one doesn't have that problem, but is a performance taking a hit by having to lookup video id in every comment document?
So what is the best way to solve this problem?
